The paper deals with approximation algorithms for geometric optimization problems, specifically covering points in the plane with fat triangles. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and approximation algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses related problems such as independent set of triangles in three dimensions, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of approximation ratios and analysis of hardness suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT).
